Day 16 – Fsociety Tool

Fsociety = Automated penetration testing toolkit
Inspired by the TV show "Mr. Robot"

Purpose:
- Combines multiple hacking tools into one framework
- Used for automation in reconnaissance & exploitation

Category:
Post-exploitation / Automation framework

What Fsociety Includes:
- Information gathering tools
- Password attacks
- Wireless attacks
- Exploitation tools
- Sniffing & spoofing tools
- Web hacking tools

Common Integrated Tools:
Nmap
Metasploit
Hydra
Aircrack-ng
Nikto
SQLmap

Why Fsociety is Important:
- Helps beginners understand tool categories
- Automates multiple tasks
- Good for lab practice
- Shows structure of penetration workflow

Risks:
- Not recommended for blind usage
- Requires understanding of each tool
- Can cause legal issues if misused

Important Concept:
Automation ≠ Skill
Real cybersecurity requires understanding what each tool does internally.

Ethical Reminder:
Use only in lab environment (Kali VM, TryHackMe, Hack The Box).
Never scan real-world systems without permission.

Key Learning:
Fsociety teaches how different tools connect in the hacking lifecycle.
